						<summary>

						<p>On the Garuḍa pillar lying on the bank of the Sagilēru.</p>						

						<p>This inscription refers to the cyclic year <hi rend="italic">Śārvari</hi> and may be assigned to the 14th century, on the basis palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It mentions the setting up of a <hi rend="italic">Garuḍa Pillar (Garuḍālvār)</hi> in front of the temple of Chennakēśava by Krāṅja Pōtarāju.</p>						

						</summary>
